gomodel:SYNGO_4021  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Figure 1: Electron micrographs showing RTN4 immunoreactivity in the spinal cord motoneurons of adult rats, detected with pre-embedding immunogold-silver cytochemistry (A-C) and post-embedding immunogold cytochemistry (D). Immunogold particles indicating RTN4 immunoreactivity could be found in dendritic profiles (Den) and in close apposition to the postsynaptic density (thin arrows in A-C) and the postsynaptic dense bodies (thin arrows in C and D) at both symmetric (thick arrow in A and B) and asymmetric synapses (thick arrow in C and D).\n\nNote on the antibody used: Antibody was generated against an RTN4 specific C-terminus 572-amino acid fragment (621-1192). The antibody is further described in PMID: 12577319.. Experimental description: Adult Sprague-Dawley rats were used for the study." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-2916-7616" ;
        dc:date           "2020-12-08" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_4021" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

